description.narrative: The;Government;received;UNICEF’s;support to improve;the;quality of;newborn and maternal health care services;in 16;tertiary;perinatal;centres;that served;125,156;newborns.;Improvement of;infrastructure, provision of 150 units of equipment and increased capacity of 660;health;care providers;in 3 most deprived;rayons/districts;of;Karakalpakstan;have;increased;20 percent of;the survival;rate;of;low-birth-weight;newborns;since;2018.;171;health;care providers;gained knowledge and skills to;deliver state-guaranteed;health benefits packages;in;the;Syrdarya;region;for 23,180 newborns.;WHO and UNICEF recommended;indicators;for evidence-based;decision;making;have;been;integrated;into;Uzbekistan;National Health;Management;Information;System.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/01/2022
